<subSubSection box="[198,1383,551,578]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,152,818]" box="[198,1383,551,578]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,551,577]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Etymology:</emphasis>
Named after my wife, Silvia (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[699,800,552,578]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Silvinha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Silvinha</taxonomicName>
) Altoé Falqueto. The name is feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,361,591,617]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Distribution:</emphasis>
Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[530,602,592,618]" name="Brazil" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Paulo" authorityName="Paulo" box="[619,743,592,618]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Sao" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">São Paulo</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[756,918,592,618]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[983,1155,592,618]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
states). Endemic to the southeastern part of the 
<collectingRegion box="[432,512,632,658]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Parana</collectingRegion>
Forest province in the 
<collectingRegion box="[783,862,632,658]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Parana</collectingRegion>
subregion (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1104,632,658]" captionStart="FIGURES 107–108" captionStartId="69.[151,269,1969,1993]" captionTargetBox="[166,1417,182,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-37@69.[166,1420,182,1945]" captionTargetPageId="69" captionText="FIGURES 107–108. Distribution maps. 107. Genieridium medinae (circles) and G. bordoni (triangles); 108. Nunoidium argentinum (circles), Pereiraidium almeidai (squares) and Silvinha unica (triangles)." pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,152,818]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,321,671,697]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Remarks:</emphasis>
This genus is related to 
<emphasis box="[609,1249,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName box="[609,734,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Trichillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trichillum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[746,888,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Besourenga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Besourenga</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="1969" box="[900,1051,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Eutrichillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eutrichillum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[1063,1245,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Degallieridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Degallieridium</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[1307,1429,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Feeridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1307,1429,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Feeridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although its exact position in that group is not resolved yet. Its main autapomorphies are the absence of organized punctation in elytral discal interstriae, uniquely shaped pseudoepipleura and clypeal teeth. See more remarks under 
<emphasis box="[326,473,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[326,469,792,817]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Besourenga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Besourenga</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
